From: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
Subject: [PATCH] dts: orangepi-zero: OTG gadget mode (otg dr_mode, drop ID detect)

Force the micro-USB OTG port usable as a USB gadget on mainline: use OTG
dr_mode and remove the PG12 id-detect GPIO (which reads as host on this board
and routes the port to the EHCI host controller instead of the musb gadget).

Signed-off-by: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
---
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h2-plus-orangepi-zero.dts	2026-06-24 23:58:56.024383589 +0200
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h2-plus-orangepi-zero.dts	2026-06-24 23:58:56.024777903 +0200
@@ -210,7 +210,7 @@
 };
 
 &usb_otg {
-	dr_mode = "peripheral";
+	dr_mode = "otg";
 	status = "okay";
 };
 
@@ -221,7 +221,6 @@
 	 * always off even if the board is powered via GPIO pins.
 	 */
 	status = "okay";
-	usb0_id_det-gpios = <&pio 6 12 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>; /* PG12 */
 };
 
 &pio {
